<!-- Modal -->
<div class="modal fade" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" id="helpDetailModal" aria-labelledby="helpDetailModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h5 class="modal-title" id="helpDetailModalLabel">
          Help
        </h5>
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
          <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body text-left">

        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-12 help">
            <strong>Movement</strong><br/>
            <span>You can move your character about by pressing <pre>W</pre>, <pre>A</pre>, <pre>S</pre>, <pre>D</pre> or
                  the corresponding <pre>up</pre>, <pre>left</pre>, <pre>down</pre>, or <pre>right</pre> arrow keys.
                  Certain tiles will block your movement, such as walls and closed doors.</span>
            <span>Holding down <pre>P</pre> and moving will allow you to pull adjacent tiles if able.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr/>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-12 help">
            <strong>Doors</strong><br/>
            <span>Doors can allow movement <pre>'</pre> (open) or block <pre>+</pre> (closed). You can attempt to open a closed door
                  (or any tile really) by pressing <pre>o</pre> followed by a direction (WASD or arrow keys). You can also attempt to
                  close an open door by pressing <pre>c</pre> followed by a direction.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr/>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-12 help">
            <strong>Use Item</strong>
            <span>Press <pre>shift</pre> and a direction to use an equipped item.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr/>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-12 help">
            <strong>Light Torch</strong>
            <span>If you have a torch, press <pre>T</pre> to light your way in the dark for a time.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr/>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-12 help">
            <strong>Equip Item</strong>
            <span>If you have other items, pressing <pre>E</pre> will bring up a modal allowing you to
                  equip a different one. Escape key cancels, or use the up and down arrow keys or use
                  the mouse to make your selection.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="modal-footer">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
